casebody.data:
Ilisha HARRIS, Appellant,
v.
DIVISION OF EMPLOYMENT SECURITY, Respondent. WD 80545 Missouri Court of Appeals, Western District. ORDER FILED: May 1, 2018 Ilisha Harris, Blue Springs, MO, Appellant Acting Pro Se. Meaghan Forck, Jefferson City, MO, Counsel for Respondent. Before Division One: Lisa White Hardwick, P.J., Thomas H. Newton, and Cynthia L. Martin, JJ.

ORDER

Per Curiam:

Ms. Ilisha Harris appeals a judgment from the Labor and Industrial Relations Commission finding that she had not demonstrated good cause for failing to call in for the telephone hearing before the Division of Employment Security. For reasons stated in the memorandum provided to the parties, we affirm. Rule 84.16(b).
